data.title: Enterprise, Utah Population History
data.meta_description: Access the most recent census population information for Enterprise, Utah, including a population profile and history.
data.text:
What is the voting age population of Enterprise, Utah?

The total voting age population of Enterprise, Utah, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 968. The voting age population is 47.9% male and 52.1% female.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah residents are senior citizens?

According to the latest census statistics, 13.8% of the residents of Enterprise are 65 or older.

What are the racial demographics of Enterprise, Utah?

The racial demographics of Enterprise are 99.1% White and 0.9% Other. Additionally, 1.3% of the population identifies as Hispanic.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah residents are below the poverty line?

In Enterprise, 8.4% of residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate is 8.1%. On a per-household basis, 4.9% of families are below the poverty line in Enterprise.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah residents are in the labor force?

Among those aged 16 and older, 53.3% of Enterprise residents are in the labor force.

What are the education levels among Enterprise, Utah residents?

Among the adult population 25 years old and over, 97.3% of Enterprise residents have at least a high school degree or equivalent, 27.5% have a bachelor's degree and 7.2% have a graduate or professional degree.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah residents speak a non-English language at home?

Among Enterprise residents aged 5 and older, 3.0% of them speak a non-English language at home. Broken down by language: 1.0% of residents speak Spanish at home, 0.0% speak an Indo-European language, and 1.5% speak an Asian language.

What is the unemployment rate in Enterprise, Utah?

The unemployment rate in Enterprise is 3.2%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah residents work for the government?

In Enterprise, 26.0% of the residents in the non-military labor force are employed by the local, state and federal government.

What is the median income in Enterprise, Utah?

The median household income in Enterprise is $58,650.

What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Enterprise, Utah?

In Enterprise, 85.7% of housing units are occupied by their owners.

What percentage of housing units are rented in Enterprise, Utah?

Renters occupy 14.3% of housing units in Enterprise.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah housing units were built before 1940?

Of all the housing units in Enterprise, 14.6% of them were build before 1940.

What percentage of Enterprise, Utah housing units were built after 2000?

In Enterprise, 18.3% of the total housing units were built after the year 2000.

What is the median monthly rent in Enterprise, Utah?

The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Enterprise is $1,005.

What percentage of households in Enterprise, Utah have broadband internet?

In Enterprise, 87.2% of households have an active broadband internet connection.
